      "*": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b><a href=\"/Main_Page\" title=\"Main Page\">Home</a> * <a href=\"/Engines\" title=\"Engines\">Engines</a> * Chenard</b>\n</p>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:302px;\"><a href=\"/File:Bundesarchiv_Bild_183-2008-0516-500,_Fernschreibmaschine_mit_Telefonanschluss.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/50/Bundesarchiv_Bild_183-2008-0516-500%2C_Fernschreibmaschine_mit_Telefonanschluss.jpg/330px-Bundesarchiv_Bild_183-2008-0516-500%2C_Fernschreibmaschine_mit_Telefonanschluss.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"204\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/50/Bundesarchiv_Bild_183-2008-0516-500%2C_Fernschreibmaschine_mit_Telefonanschluss.jpg/500px-Bundesarchiv_Bild_183-2008-0516-500%2C_Fernschreibmaschine_mit_Telefonanschluss.jpg 1.5x, https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/5/50/Bundesarchiv_Bild_183-2008-0516-500%2C_Fernschreibmaschine_mit_Telefonanschluss.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/File:Bundesarchiv_Bild_183-2008-0516-500,_Fernschreibmaschine_mit_Telefonanschluss.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Early Teletype <sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></div></div></div> \n<p><b>Chenard</b>,<br />\nan <a href=\"/Category:Open_Source\" title=\"Category:Open Source\">open source chess program</a> by <a href=\"/Don_Cross\" title=\"Don Cross\">Don Cross</a>, written in <a href=\"/Cpp\" title=\"Cpp\">C++</a>. Its development already started in 1993, and it is maintained and improved until the present. \nThe source code of the didactic program is well structured and documented, is in the <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Public_domain\">public domain</a> with attribution of author's name and web address required in distributed works <sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>. \nA <a href=\"/Windows\" title=\"Windows\">Windows</a> version comes with an own <a href=\"/GUI\" title=\"GUI\">GUI</a>, other versions for <a href=\"/Windows\" title=\"Windows\">Windows</a> and <a href=\"/Linux\" title=\"Linux\">Linux</a> support the <a href=\"/Chess_Engine_Communication_Protocol\" title=\"Chess Engine Communication Protocol\">Chess Engine Communication Protocol</a> aka <a href=\"/WinBoard\" title=\"WinBoard\">WinBoard</a> or <a href=\"/XBoard\" title=\"XBoard\">XBoard</a>, its own native <a href=\"/CLI\" title=\"CLI\">command line interface</a>, or <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Teleprinter\">teletype</a> chess. \n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Description\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Description</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Search\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Search</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Evaluation\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Evaluation</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#EGDB\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">EGDB</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#Screen_Shot\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Screen Shot</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#See_also\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">See also</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#Forum_Posts\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Forum Posts</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-8\"><a href=\"#External_Links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External Links</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-9\"><a href=\"#Chess_Program\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Chess Program</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-10\"><a href=\"#Misc\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Misc</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-11\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">6</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Description\">Description</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Chenard&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Description\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<p>Chenard provides a <a href=\"/Genetic_Programming#GeneticAlgorithm\" title=\"Genetic Programming\">genetic algorithm</a> framework for evolving <a href=\"/Move_Ordering\" title=\"Move Ordering\">move ordering</a> and <a href=\"/Evaluation\" title=\"Evaluation\">evaluation</a> heuristics. \nThe <a href=\"/Board_Representation\" title=\"Board Representation\">board is represented</a> by a <a href=\"/Mailbox\" title=\"Mailbox\">12x12 mailbox</a> with <a href=\"/Pieces#DisjointPieceFlags\" title=\"Pieces\">disjoint piece flag encoding</a>. \nSince Chenard isn't <a href=\"/Negamax\" title=\"Negamax\">negamaxing</a>, <a href=\"/Search\" title=\"Search\">search</a>, evaluation as well as <a href=\"/Move_Generation\" title=\"Move Generation\">move generation</a> routines are implemented separately for White and Black. \n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Search\">Search</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Chenard&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Search\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Chenard's <a href=\"/Search\" title=\"Search\">search</a> is pure <a href=\"/Alpha-Beta\" title=\"Alpha-Beta\">alpha-beta</a> with <a href=\"/Transposition_Table\" title=\"Transposition Table\">transposition table</a>, \ndespite <a href=\"/Quiescence_Search\" title=\"Quiescence Search\">quiescence search</a> and its top layer with <a href=\"/Quiescence_Search#Checks\" title=\"Quiescence Search\">checks</a>, \nwithout any <a href=\"/Selectivity\" title=\"Selectivity\">selectivity</a> in form of <a href=\"/Extensions\" title=\"Extensions\">extensions</a>, <a href=\"/Pruning\" title=\"Pruning\">forward pruning</a> and <a href=\"/Reductions\" title=\"Reductions\">reductions</a>. \nThe <a href=\"/Root\" title=\"Root\">root</a> search implements <a href=\"/Iterative_Deepening\" title=\"Iterative Deepening\">iterative deepening</a> without <a href=\"/Aspiration_Windows\" title=\"Aspiration Windows\">aspiration windows</a>. \nThe <a href=\"/Depth\" title=\"Depth\">depth</a> parameter, suited to index a <a href=\"/Ply\" title=\"Ply\">ply</a> <a href=\"/Stack\" title=\"Stack\">stack</a>, starts at the root with zero and is incremented through the indirect <a href=\"/Recursion\" title=\"Recursion\">recursive</a> function calls until the the maximum depth, dubbed level, is reached and quiescence is called <sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>. \n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Evaluation\">Evaluation</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Chenard&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Evaluation\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The <a href=\"/Evaluation\" title=\"Evaluation\">evaluation</a> looks sophisticated considering a bunch of features, many part of Chenard's genes. \nBeside the aggregation of <a href=\"/Material\" title=\"Material\">material</a>, imbalance terms and <a href=\"/Piece-Square_Tables\" title=\"Piece-Square Tables\">piece-square tables</a>, \nwhich decides on an early exit aka <a href=\"/Lazy_Evaluation\" title=\"Lazy Evaluation\">lazy evaluation</a>, Chenard looks at <a href=\"/Trapped_Pieces\" title=\"Trapped Pieces\">immobile</a> and <a href=\"/Connectivity\" title=\"Connectivity\">connected</a> pieces, \nalong with various <a href=\"/Evaluation_of_Pieces\" title=\"Evaluation of Pieces\">piece specific evaluation features</a>, and further takes <a href=\"/Pawn_Structure\" title=\"Pawn Structure\">pawn structure</a> with focus on <a href=\"/Passed_Pawn\" title=\"Passed Pawn\">passed pawns</a>, <a href=\"/King_Safety\" title=\"King Safety\">king safety</a>, and even <a href=\"/Tactics\" title=\"Tactics\">tactical motives</a> such as <a href=\"/Pin\" title=\"Pin\">pinned pieces</a> and <a href=\"/Double_Attack\" title=\"Double Attack\">forks</a> into account. \nBeside, Chenard has a <a href=\"/index.php?title=Mop-up_evaluation&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Mop-up evaluation (page does not exist)\">mop-up evaluation</a> for late endgames like <a href=\"/KBNK_Endgame\" title=\"KBNK Endgame\">KBNK</a>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"EGDB\">EGDB</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Chenard&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: EGDB\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Chenard has its own <a href=\"/Endgame_Tablebases#DTM\" title=\"Endgame Tablebases\">depth to mate</a> <a href=\"/Endgame_Tablebases\" title=\"Endgame Tablebases\">endgame databases</a>, generator and probing code <sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> <sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> <sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>.\n</p>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Screen_Shot\">Screen Shot</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Chenard&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: Screen Shot\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<div class=\"floatnone\"><a href=\"http://cosinekitty.com/chenard/\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img alt=\"Chenard screen shot.jpg\" src=\"/images/5/58/Chenard_screen_shot.jpg\" width=\"618\" height=\"482\" style=\"vertical-align: text-bottom\" class=\"thumbborder\" /></a></div> \n<p>Chenard's <a href=\"/Windows\" title=\"Windows\">Windows</a> <a href=\"/GUI\" title=\"GUI\">GUI</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup> \n</p>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Chenard&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<ul><li> <a href=\"/index.php?title=Flywheel&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Flywheel (page does not exist)\">Flywheel</a></li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Forum_Posts\">Forum Posts</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Chenard&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" title=\"Edit section: Forum Posts\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=20846\">Chenard 1.136 with Winboard support available</a> by <a href=\"/Jim_Ablett\" title=\"Jim Ablett\">Jim Ablett</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, April 26, 2008</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=21252\">Chenard 1.1.40 JA</a> by <a href=\"/Harun_Taner\" title=\"Harun Taner\">Harun Taner</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, May 20, 2008</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=29749\">Chenard</a> by <a href=\"/Gabor_Szots\" title=\"Gabor Szots\">Gabor Szots</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, September 14, 2009</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum3/viewtopic.php?f=2&amp;t=61386\">an oldy but goody, Chenard for the Mac - xBoard with source</a> by <a href=\"/Michael_Byrne\" title=\"Michael Byrne\">MikeB</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, September 10, 2016</li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_Links\">External Links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Chenard&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8\" title=\"Edit section: External Links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Chess_Program\">Chess Program</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Chenard&amp;action=edit&amp;section=9\" title=\"Edit section: Chess Program\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://cosinekitty.com/chenard/\">Chenard - a freeware chess program</a> by <a href=\"/Don_Cross\" title=\"Don Cross\">Don Cross</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://github.com/cosinekitty/chenard\">cosinekitty/chenard · GitHub</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.computerchess.org.uk/ccrl/404/cgi/compare_engines.cgi?family=Chenard&amp;print=Rating+list&amp;print=Results+table&amp;print=LOS+table&amp;print=Ponder+hit+table&amp;print=Eval+difference+table&amp;print=Comopp+gamenum+table&amp;print=Overlap+table&amp;print=Score+with+common+opponents\">Chenard</a> at <a href=\"/CCRL\" title=\"CCRL\">CCRL 40/4</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Misc\">Misc</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Chenard&amp;action=edit&amp;section=10\" title=\"Edit section: Misc\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chenard-Walcker\">Chenard-Walcker from Wikipedia</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Louis_Chenard\">Louis Chenard from Wikipedia</a></li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Chenard&amp;action=edit&amp;section=11\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Bundesarchiv_Bild_183-2008-0516-500,_Fernschreibmaschine_mit_Telefonanschluss.jpg?uselang=en\">A Creed Model 7 teleprinter in 1930</a>, Photo by Willi Illger, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Commons:Bundesarchiv\">Bundesarchiv</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.bild.bundesarchiv.de/dba/de/search/?query=Bild+183-2008-0516-500\">Bild 183-2008-0516-500</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/de/deed.en\">CC BY-SA 3.0 DE</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikimedia_Commons\">Wikimedia Commons</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fernschreiber\">Fernschreiber - Wikipedia.de</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://cosinekitty.com/chenard/\">Chenard - a freeware chess program</a> by <a href=\"/Don_Cross\" title=\"Don Cross\">Don Cross</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://github.com/cosinekitty/chenard/blob/master/src/search.cpp\">chenard/search.cpp at master · cosinekitty/chenard · GitHub</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://github.com/cosinekitty/endgame\">GitHub - cosinekitty/endgame: Chess endgame database generator</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-5\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://github.com/cosinekitty/chenard/blob/master/src/egdbase.cpp\">chenard/egdbase.cpp at master · cosinekitty/chenard · GitHub</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-6\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://levelup.gitconnected.com/build-your-own-chess-endgame-monster-a3fb23bb3ec1\">Build Your Own Chess Endgame Monster - Level Up Coding</a> by <a href=\"/Don_Cross\" title=\"Don Cross\">Don Cross</a>, February 17, 2020</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-7\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-7\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"htt